						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the village.</p>						

						<p>18th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to the 18th century A.D. on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Records an invocation of <hi rend="italic">Ghaṇṭākarna</hi> for warding of the disease of cattle and refers to Sahadēva, also known as Tantrīpāla, one of the Pāṇḍavas who treats the cows of Virāṭapaṭṭaṇa.</p>						

						</summary>
